        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 8:51PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 851 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cotulla. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cotulla, Los Angeles, and Gardendale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
